            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Water damage and mould remediation</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Leaks, burst pipes and failed waterproofing can cause ceiling damage, wall saturation and mould growth. Quick response within 48 hours reduces secondary damage and reinstatement costs.
            </p>
            <a href="/blog/commercial-water-damage-mould-remediation-melbourne" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">
              Learn more →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Fire and Smoke Damage -->
        <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img
            src="/images/learn/fire-damage-thumb.svg"
            alt="Fire and smoke damage restoration thumbnail placeholder 300x200"
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
            width="300"
            height="200"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Fire and smoke damage restoration</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Fire and smoke affect structural elements, electrical systems and air quality. Restoration includes make safe works, cleaning, odour removal and rebuilding damaged areas.
            </p>
            <a href="/blog/fire-damage-restoration" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">
              Learn more →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Structural Remediation -->
        <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img
            src="/images/learn/structural-thumb.svg"
            alt="Structural remediation and concrete spalling thumbnail placeholder 300x200"
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
            width="300"
            height="200"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Structural remediation and concrete spalling</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Concrete cancer, spalling and structural cracks compromise building integrity. Remediation involves removing damaged concrete, treating reinforcement and rebuilding to engineering specifications.
            </p>
            <a href="/blog/concrete-cancer-prevention-remediation" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">
              Learn more →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Facade and Cladding -->
        <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img
            src="/images/learn/facade-cladding-thumb.svg"
            alt="Facade and cladding defect remediation thumbnail placeholder 300x200"
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
            width="300"
            height="200"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Facade and cladding defect remediation</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Non-compliant cladding, failed seals and water ingress through facades require removal, compliance upgrades and weatherproofing. Often involves building surveyor approval and staged works.
            </p>
            <a href="/blog/facade-cladding-remediation-fireproof-compliance" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">
              Learn more →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Make Safe and Emergency Works -->
        <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img
            src="/images/learn/make-safe-thumb.svg"
            alt="Make safe and emergency works thumbnail placeholder 300x200"
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
            width="300"
            height="200"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Make safe and emergency works</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Urgent response to electrical hazards, structural instability and safety risks. Make safe works isolate danger, secure the site and allow assessment before full remediation begins.
            </p>
            <a href="/blog/electrical-make-safe" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">
              Learn more →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Ceiling Failures -->
        <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img
            src="/images/learn/ceiling-leaks-thumb.svg"
            alt="Leak related ceiling failures thumbnail placeholder 300x200"
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
            width="300"
            height="200"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Leak related ceiling failures</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Roof leaks, HVAC condensate and plumbing failures cause ceiling grid collapse, tile staining and insulation saturation. Remediation includes source repair, drying and ceiling replacement.
            </p>
