  <!-- The Commercial Remediation Process -->
  <section id="remediation-process" class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">The commercial remediation process</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-8">
          While every project is different, most commercial remediation works follow a similar sequence from initial assessment through to handover.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
          <div>
            <ol class="space-y-6">
              <li class="flex gap-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">
                  1
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Assess and make safe</h3>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                    Identify the damage, isolate hazards and secure the site. This may include electrical isolation, structural propping or containment barriers.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">
                  2
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Contain and isolate where required</h3>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                    Set up barriers, negative air pressure or access restrictions to prevent contamination spread and allow occupied areas to remain operational.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">
                  3
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Drying and moisture control</h3>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                    For water related damage, drying equipment and moisture monitoring reduce secondary issues like mould and material degradation.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          <div>
            <ol class="space-y-6" start="4">
              <li class="flex gap-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">
                  4
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Salvage versus strip out decisions</h3>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                    Determine what can be cleaned or repaired and what needs replacement. Factors include contamination level, cost and time constraints.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">
                  5
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Reinstatement and handover</h3>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                    Rebuild or restore affected areas, complete compliance testing and provide handover documentation including warranties and test certificates.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-muted/30 rounded-lg p-8">
          <img
            src="/images/learn/remediation-process-diagram.svg"
            alt="Commercial remediation process diagram placeholder 600x400"
            class="w-full max-w-2xl mx-auto h-auto rounded-lg"
            width="600"
            height="400"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Compliance, Safety and Waste Handling -->
  <section id="compliance-safety" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-muted/30">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Compliance, safety and waste handling</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-8">
          Commercial remediation work is subject to building codes, workplace health and safety regulations and environmental requirements.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Safe work practices</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Remediation contractors work under SafeWork Victoria requirements. This includes site inductions, hazard identification, PPE, working at heights permits and confined space protocols where relevant.
            </p>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              For occupied buildings, works are often staged or scheduled outside business hours to reduce disruption and maintain safety separation between trades and building users.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Hazardous materials and waste disposal</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Remediation may involve asbestos, lead paint, contaminated materials or chemical residues. Licensed removalists and EPA approved disposal methods are required for regulated waste.
            </p>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              Waste tracking, manifests and disposal certificates form part of the handover documentation. Learn more about <a href="/blog/waste-management-sustainability" class="text-primary hover:underline">waste management and sustainability</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

